Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph <chapter-uri> move

chapter move

Purpose:
  Move one existing chapter to a new parent or sibling position.

Usage:
  wikigraph <chapter-uri> move --parent <id> [--first|--last] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri> move --root [--first|--last] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri> move --before <id> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri> move --after <id> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri> move --first [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri> move --last [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]

Behavior:
  - Moves only the chapter tree node. Source text, Reading Graph data, and summary stay attached to the same chapter id.
  - `--parent <id>` moves the chapter under another chapter.
  - `--root` moves the chapter to the top level.
  - `--before <id>` or `--after <id>` moves the chapter next to the target chapter.
  - `--first` or `--last` moves within the target parent when combined with `--parent` or `--root`.
  - Without `--parent` or `--root`, `--first` and `--last` reorder within the current parent.
  - Cannot move a chapter into or next to its own descendant.
  - Does not call an LLM provider.

Examples:
  wikigraph wkg://book.sdpub/chapter/8 move --parent 3 --first
  wikigraph wkg://book.sdpub/chapter/8 move --root --last
  wikigraph wkg://book.sdpub/chapter/8 move --before 9

See also:
  - wikigraph wkg://book.sdpub/chapter list --help
  - wikigraph wkg://book.sdpub/chapter/tree get --help
  - wikigraph help command
